Topic: OIR Test (Non-Verbal Reasoning)

Today is VERY IMPORTANT ⚠️
Most candidates lose marks here because they don’t practice patterns.

1️⃣ What is Non-Verbal Reasoning?

It tests your visual intelligence 👁️
👉 No language, only figures, shapes, patterns

You must:

Observe quickly

Identify pattern

Answer in seconds

2️⃣ Types of Non-Verbal Questions
🔷 1. Series Completion (Figures)

👉 Shapes change in:

Rotation

Size

Direction

🧠 Trick: Look for movement or rotation

🔷 2. Odd One Out

👉 One figure will be different:

Extra line

Different angle

Broken symmetry

🔷 3. Mirror Image

👉 Imagine a mirror on left/right

🧠 Trick:

Left ↔ Right reversed

Top & bottom same

🔷 4. Water Image

👉 Reflection in water

🧠 Trick:

Top ↔ Bottom reversed

Left & right same

🔷 5. Paper Folding & Cutting

👉 Paper is folded and cut
👉 Predict final holes

🧠 Trick:

Multiply cuts by folds

🔷 6. Embedded Figures

👉 Find small shape inside big one

🧠 Trick:

Focus only on required shape

3️⃣ Solving Strategy (GAME CHANGER)

🧠 Rule 1: Observe → Don’t overthink
🧠 Rule 2: Eliminate wrong options fast
🧠 Rule 3: Max 10–15 sec per question
🧠 Rule 4: Skip if stuck

👉 Speed = Selection

4️⃣ Common Mistakes

❌ Guessing without observing pattern
❌ Ignoring rotation direction
❌ Confusing mirror vs water image

5️⃣ Mini Practice

Try mentally (fast 👇)

Q1

A square rotates 90° each step → what comes next?

Q2

Which is different?
(All shapes same except one rotated differently)

Q3

If mirror is placed on right side → what happens?

Q4

Paper folded twice and cut once → how many holes?

